---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Is OW a Scrabble Word? — Yes, Valid for 5 Points"
  description="OW is a valid Scrabble word in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries, scoring 5 points (O=1, W=4). An exclamation of pain. Extensions: OWE, OWL, OWN, OWS. Free word checker."
  keywords="is ow a scrabble word, ow scrabble, ow valid word, ow points scrabble, two letter words with w, ow extensions, owl owe own scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Is OW a Scrabble Word? — Yes, Valid for 5 Points",
    "description": "OW is a valid Scrabble word in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries, scoring 5 points (O=1, W=4). An exclamation of pain.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-29",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-ow-a-scrabble-word" }
  })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is OW a valid Scrabble word?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes! OW is valid in both TWL (North American) and SOWPODS (international) dictionaries. It scores 5 points (O=1, W=4) and is an exclamation expressing pain or surprise. It's one of the most useful 2-letter words for placing the W tile." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What words can you extend OW into?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "OW extends into OWE (6pts), OWL (6pts), OWN (6pts), OWS (6pts), and OWT (6pts SOWPODS). Longer extensions include OWED, OWES, OWLS, OWNS, OWER, and OWSE. These hooks make OW strategically valuable beyond its base 5 points." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What does OW mean in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "OW is an exclamation used to express sudden pain, like when you stub your toe. It functions as an interjection in English. Despite being informal speech, it's a fully valid Scrabble word in all official dictionaries." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Checker</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is OW a Scrabble Word? — Yes, Valid for 5 Points</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>3 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <!-- Green Hero Card -->
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-green-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-950/30 to-emerald-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-green-500/70">✓ Valid</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">OW — 5 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-green-300 font-semibold mb-3">O=1, W=4 · Valid in TWL ✓ · Valid in SOWPODS ✓</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">An exclamation of pain. One of the essential 2-letter words for placing your W tile efficiently in parallel plays and tight board positions.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Base Score</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">W=4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Key Tile</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Extensions</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Both</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Dictionaries</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Definition & Usage</h2>
      <p>OW is an interjection expressing sudden pain or surprise — the sound you make when you stub your toe. It's informal speech that's been accepted into all official Scrabble dictionaries.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-cyan-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">📖 Dictionary Entry</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200"><span class="text-white font-medium">OW</span> (interjection) — used to express sudden pain. Also spelled "ow!" Variant of "ouch." Valid in competitive play since its inclusion in the Official Scrabble Players Dictionary.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Extensions from OW</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OWE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OWL</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OWN</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OWS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OWED</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OWLS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OWNS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">W placement:</span> OW is your go-to for placing W (4pts) when the board is tight. Play it parallel to an existing word for bonus crossword points on both letters.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Hook into OWL/OWN/OWE:</span> Play OW first, then extend it next turn into OWL, OWN, or OWE. This lets you score twice from the same position — once for OW, once for the extension.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Front hooks:</span> BOW (8pts), COW (8pts), HOW (9pts), LOW (6pts), MOW (8pts), NOW (6pts), ROW (6pts), SOW (6pts), TOW (6pts), VOW (9pts), WOW (9pts) — OW accepts many front hooks for extra scoring.</p></div>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/is-aw-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is AW a Scrabble Word?</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/is-we-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is WE a Scrabble Word?</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word instantly — free Scrabble word checker, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
